      },
      "lineNbr": 44,
      "author": {
        "id": 5633
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-05-08T17:36:42Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "The octagon is the intersection of fBounds and fBounds45, which means fBounds is the bounding box of the octagon.\n\nIf we want the integer bounding box of the octagon, then we round out the bounding box, i.e., round out fBounds.\n\n(And fBounds is fully tightened around the octagon by requirement, so there\u0027s no way we could make it tighter by looking at fBounds45.)",
      "parentUuid": "bdb10481_50d3cd08",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 44,
        "startChar": 40,
        "endLine": 44,
        "endChar": 63
      },
